The paper discusses the difficulties of training sparse neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on sparse ResNet-50 architectures trained on the ImageNet-2012 dataset, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses optimization dynamics and energy landscapes, which are topics that fall under the subfield of deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the need to traverse extra dimensions to escape stationary points, which suggests a focus on optimization algorithms (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses the ImageNet-2012 dataset, which is a commonly used dataset in natural language processing (cs.CL), although this is less likely to be the primary focus of the paper.
